The licensing requirements for a home inspector may be waived for a person moving to Kentucky from another jurisdiction, and the person may be granted a license as a home inspector if:
The other jurisdiction grants the same privileges to licensees of Kentucky as Kentucky grants to licensees of that other jurisdiction;
The person is licensed in the other jurisdiction;
The licensing requirements of the other jurisdiction are determined by the board to be substantially similar to the requirements of KRS 198B.700 to 198B.738; and
The person states that he or she has studied, is familiar with, and will abide by KRS 198B.700 to 198B.738 and the administrative regulations promulgated by the board.
